geneIDs1 <- ensembldb::select(EnsDb.Mmusculus.v79, keys= rownames(res), keytype = "GENEID", columns = c("SYMBOL","GENEID"))

resOrdered <- res[base::order(res$pvalue),]
resOrdered_with_norm_counts <- merge(as.data.frame(resOrdered), ddscount, by = 'row.names', all =TRUE)

Overlapping with Gecko screen data from Salvr

SP1_repressors <- read.csv("SP1_repressor_list.csv")
RBM3_repressors <- read.csv("RBM3_repressor_list.csv")
SP1_activators <- read.csv("SP1_activator_list.csv")

library(GeneOverlap)

#Capitalising mouse gene symbols so they match with human

Uppercase_temp_DEGs <- toupper(resOrdered_with_norm_counts$gene)
RNAseq_sig_DEGs <- resOrdered_with_norm_counts
RNAseq_sig_DEGs$Uppercase.gene <- Uppercase_temp_DEGs


olap <- function(gecko_list, DEGs){
    olap1 <- newGeneOverlap(gecko_list$Gene.Symbol,DEGs$Uppercase.gene, spec =c("mm9.gene"))
    olap1 <- testGeneOverlap(olap1)
    print(olap1)
    
    overlapping_genes <- gecko_list[gecko_list$Gene.Symbol %in% DEGs$Uppercase.gene,]
    overlapping_genes$RNAseq_adj_pval <- DEGs$padj[base::match(overlapping_genes$Gene.Symbol,DEGs$Uppercase.gene)]
    overlapping_genes$RNAseq_log2fc <-  DEGs$log2FoldChange[base::match(overlapping_genes$Gene.Symbol,DEGs$Uppercase.gene)]
    return(overlapping_genes)
}


SP1_repressor_RNAseq_olap <- olap(SP1_repressors, RNAseq_sig_DEGs)

Making lists of up- and down-regulated genes at 32C

Also, calculating overlap with SMYD5 KO DEGs

Temp_upregulated <- RNAseq_sig_DEGs[RNAseq_sig_DEGs$log2FoldChange > 0,]
Temp_downregulated <- RNAseq_sig_DEGs[RNAseq_sig_DEGs$log2FoldChange < 0,]

SMYD5_KO_up <- read.csv("SMYD5_KO_upregulated.csv")
SMYD5_KO_down <- read.csv("SMYD5_KO_downregulated.csv")


olap2 <- function(temp_list, list2){
    olap1 <- newGeneOverlap(temp_list$Row.names,list2$Row.names, spec =c("mm9.gene"))
    olap1 <- testGeneOverlap(olap1)
    print(olap1)
    
    overlapping_genes <- temp_list[temp_list$Row.names %in% list2$Row.names,]
    overlapping_genes$SMYD5_adj_pval <- list2$padj[base::match(overlapping_genes$Row.names,list2$Row.names)]
    overlapping_genes$SMYD5_log2fc <-  list2$log2FoldChange[base::match(overlapping_genes$Row.names,list2$Row.names)]
    overlapping_genes <- overlapping_genes[,c(1,8,2,3,6,7,17:18)]
    colnames(overlapping_genes) <- c("ensgene", "gene","temp_baseMean", "temp_log2fc", "temp_pvalue", "temp_adj_pval", "SMYD5_adj_pval", "SMYD5_log2fc")
    return(overlapping_genes)
}
Temp_up_SMYD5_down_olap <- olap2(Temp_upregulated, SMYD5_KO_down)

Prepping data for Gene Set Enrichment Analysis (GSEA)

GSEA was used to identify significantly enriched gene sets within our RNAseq data. For this, we generated ranked gene lists comprising all detected genes assigned to a rank value. The rank value was calculated as -log10(q-value) (sign of fold change). The genes were then ranked from the highest rank value to the lowest. These lists were generated in R:

all.preranked.score <- all_detected_genes[,c(1,8,7,3)]
all.preranked.score.up <- filter(all.preranked.score, log2FoldChange >0)
all.preranked.score.up$score <- log10(1/all.preranked.score.up$padj)

all.preranked.score.down <- filter(all.preranked.score, log2FoldChange < 0)
all.preranked.score.down$score <- -log10(1/all.preranked.score.down$padj)

all.preranked.score.final <- rbind(all.preranked.score.up, all.preranked.score.down)
all.preranked.score.final <- all.preranked.score.final[,c(1,5)]
all.preranked.score.final <- all.preranked.score.final[order(-all.preranked.score.final$score),]
write.csv(all.preranked.score.final, "Temp_preranked_genelist.csv")

head(all.preranked.score.final)
##            Row.names     score
## 1 ENSMUSG00000045193 140.15866
## 2 ENSMUSG00000021134  61.64291
## 3 ENSMUSG00000042659  60.55915
## 4 ENSMUSG00000031167  55.51136
## 5 ENSMUSG00000020393  53.26689
## 6 ENSMUSG00000052397  52.97804

This file was then opened in excel, headers of all columns were deleted as well as all columns except for gene names and score. The file was saved as a tab-delimited .txt rile with the .rnk extension. This was then loaded into GSEA preranked program. We used the following settings:

Gene set: ftp.broadinstitute.org://pub/gsea/msigdb/mouse/gene_sets/mh.all.v2022.1.Mm.symbols.gmt
Collapse/remap to gene symbols: No_Collapse
Chip platform: ftp.broadinstitute.org://pub/gsea/msigdb/mouse/annotations/Mouse_Ensembl_Gene_ID_MSigDB.v2022.1.Mm.chip
Number of Permutations: 1000 
Enrichment statistic: classic 
Max size: 5000 
Min size: 15 
Normalisation mode: meandiv

Plotting GSEA results

Now we will make bar graphs of GSEA results:

Cold_pos_GSEA <- read.delim("20230112_Temp_mouse_NPCs.GseaPreranked.1673517190274/gsea_report_for_na_pos_1673517190274.tsv")
Cold_pos_GSEA.sig <- Cold_pos_GSEA[Cold_pos_GSEA$FDR.q.val < 0.25,]

Cold_neg_GSEA <- read.delim("20230112_Temp_mouse_NPCs.GseaPreranked.1673517190274/gsea_report_for_na_neg_1673517190274.tsv")
Cold_neg_GSEA.sig <- Cold_neg_GSEA[Cold_neg_GSEA$FDR.q.val < 0.25,]

Cold_GSEA.sig <- rbind(Cold_pos_GSEA.sig, Cold_neg_GSEA.sig)
Cold_GSEA.sig <- Cold_GSEA.sig[order(Cold_GSEA.sig$NES),]

Cold_GSEA_forGraph <- Cold_GSEA.sig[,c(1,6)]
Cold_GSEA_forGraph$NAME <- gsub('HALLMARK_','',Cold_GSEA_forGraph$NAME)

barplot(Cold_GSEA_forGraph$NES, horiz=TRUE, names.arg = Cold_GSEA_forGraph$NAME, las =1, xlim = c(-4,4), cex.names = 0.5, col = "darkblue")

par(mar=c(6,12,4,4)+0.1)


pdf(file="Temp_GSEA.pdf", height = 3, width = 3, pointsize = 0.1)
par(mar=c(6,12,4,4)+0.1, lwd = 0.2)
barplot(Cold_GSEA_forGraph$NES, horiz=TRUE, names.arg = Cold_GSEA_forGraph$NAME, 
        xlab = c("Normalized enrichment score"), las =1, xlim = c(-4,4), border = NA, cex.names = 0.5, col = "darkblue")
dev.off()
